      <div class="disclaimer">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Lulu is not a veterinary service and does not provide diagnosis, treatment, or professional veterinary advice. For medical concerns about your pet, please contact a licensed veterinarian.
      </div>

      <p>Lulu is a pet health journal for cat and dog owners. Use it to track daily check-ins, maintain health logs, and generate PDF reports for veterinarian visits.</p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <div class="contact-card">
        <p>For app support, account questions, privacy requests, account deletion help, or feedback:</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a class="contact-email" href="mailto:support@lulu.pet">support@lulu.pet</a></p>
        <p>We aim to respond within a few business days.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Common Topics</h2>

      <div class="topic-cards">
        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Account &amp; sign-in</h3>
          <p>Lulu uses secure authentication through Supabase. If you have trouble signing in, try resetting your password through the app’s sign-in flow. If problems continue, email us with the address associated with your account.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Deleting your account</h3>
          <p>You can delete your account from within the Lulu app. Account deletion is intended to remove your account, pet profiles, photos, check-ins, health logs, and associated journal data from our active services, subject to reasonable processing time and limited retention required for backups, security, or legal compliance. Deletion may take some time to complete across our systems. If you cannot access the app, contact us at the email above and we will assist you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Pet profiles &amp; health logs</h3>
          <p>You can add pet information such as name, species, breed, age, weight, photo, and notes. Daily check-ins cover appetite, energy, mood, stool, vomiting, symptoms, medication, behavior, and general observations. You can also create separate health logs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>PDF reports</h3>
          <p>You can generate PDF reports from your pet’s journal data and share them using your device’s sharing options. Please review reports before sharing. You are responsible for choosing recipients and for how shared information is used.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Notifications &amp; reminders</h3>
          <p>If you enable reminders, Lulu uses your device’s local notification system. You can turn notifications off in your device settings or within the app, where available. Reminders are for convenience only and are not medical alerts.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Data &amp; privacy</h3>
          <p>For details on what information we handle and how it is stored, see our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>. Lulu does not sell user data, does not use third-party advertising, and does not use tracking in the current version.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Free &amp; Premium features</h3>
          <p>Lulu may introduce premium features in the future. The initial iOS release may not include in-app payments. Any paid features will be described in the app before purchase.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

